ldren and society than good.The Perversion of Youth critiques the current system and its methods for treating and categorizing juveniles, and calls for a major reevaluation of how these cases should be managed in the future. Through an analysis of the history of the problem and an empirical review of the literature, including specific cases and their outcomes, DiCataldo demonstrates that current practices are based more on our collective fears and moral passions than on any supportive science or sound policy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aTeenage sex offendersxPsychology. 0aTeenage sex offendersxRehabilitation. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / Developmental / Adolescent.2bisacsh  aDiCataldo.  aMany.  aand.  abeing.  acautions.  achildren.  adeal.  adoing.  aempirical.  agood.  aharm.  ahave.  ajuvenile.  amore.  aoffenders.  asociety.  astrategies.  asupport.  athan.  atoday.  aused.  awith.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070644440uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814720011.001.0001zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814785225zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814785225/original  a978-3-11-070644-4 New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA